Creates a [Pixi Application](https://pixijs.download/release/docs/PIXI.Application.html).

Just like its native Pixi counterpart, it sets up the [Renderer](/docs/components/renderer), [Ticker](/docs/components/ticker) and root [Container](/docs/components/container). If you wish, you can manually render those components instead.

## Usage

```svelte example csr noApp
<script>
  import { Application, Text } from 'svelte-pixi'
</script>

<Application width={400} height={400} antialias>
  <Text
    x={200}
    y={200}
    anchor={0.5}
    text="Hello World"
    style={{ fill: 'white'}}
  />
</Application>
```

## Custom View

If you want to customize the element that the canvas is rendered into, you can use the `view` slot. The canvas will be appended as a child of the slot element.

```svelte example csr noApp
<script>
  import { Application, Text } from 'svelte-pixi'
</script>

<Application width={400} height={400} antialias>
  <div slot="view" class="custom">
    <!-- canvas will be placed here -->
  </div>

  <!-- pixi components go here -->
  <Text
    x={200}
    y={200}
    anchor={0.5}
    text="Hello World"
    style={{ fill: 'white'}}
  />
</Application>

<style>
  .custom :global(canvas) {
    border: 5px solid tomato;
    border-radius: 5px;
  }
</style>
```

